      Method
      Description
      com.ibm.cuda.CudaDevice.getDriverVersion()
      Use Cuda.getDriverVersion() instead.

      Use Cuda.getRuntimeVersion() instead.
      com.ibm.dtfj.java.j9.JavaObject.createJavaObject(JavaRuntime, ImagePointer)
      Use JavaRuntime.getObjectAtAddress(ImagePointer) instead
      com.ibm.dtfj.java.j9.JavaObject.createJavaObject(JavaRuntime, ImagePointer, JavaHeap, JavaHeapRegion)

      invalid reference 
      JavaRuntime#getObjectInHeapRegion(ImagePointer,JavaHeap,JavaHeapRegion)
      instead

      com.ibm.dtfj.java.JavaField.isNestedPackedArray()

      Use "getVersion()" instead
      com.ibm.gpu.CUDAManager.getInstance()
      Use instance() instead.
      com.ibm.gpu.CUDAManager.tearDown()
      This method has no effect; it will be removed in a future version.
      com.ibm.j9ddr.vm29.tools.ddrinteractive.JavaVersionHelper.ensureJava9AndUp(J9JavaVMPointer, PrintStream)
      use JavaVersionHelper.ensureMinimumJavaVersion(int, J9JavaVMPointer, PrintStream) instead
      com.ibm.jvm.trace.format.api.TraceContext.setTraceType(int)
      this method is deprecated as it's use implies a problem elsewhere
      com.ibm.jvm.Trace.getMicros()
      Use System.nanoTime() instead as this provides as good or better resolution and is more portable.
      com.ibm.jvm.Trace.initializeTrace()
      this method does nothing
      com.ibm.oti.shared.SharedClassCacheInfo.isCachePersistent()
      Use getCacheType() instead.

      Use findHelpersForClassLoader(ClassLoader loader) instead.
